seed_chunks:
Saltmarrow Cemetery is “maintained” by the Lanternward Society, a civic-minded guild of caretakers and historians who host tasteful tours—while quietly editing headstones and burial ledgers to erase certain names. Across town, the Ashford & Daughters Mourning House offers impeccable funerals and grief counsel, yet keeps a private annex of unsanctioned records and relics tied to disappearances along the coast. Threaded through both is the Brine-Choir, a harmless-seeming tide-singers’ charity that blesses sailors’ graves, but actually trades in drowned secrets, using buoy-bells to signal meetings and bargains. The Lanternward leans on Ashford for discretion; Ashford fears the Choir’s reach; the Choir blackmails both, and the cemetery itself keeps score.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "The Lanternward Society",
      "public_front": "A respected guild of cemetery caretakers, local historians, and lantern-lighters who preserve Saltmarrow’s heritage and run guided tours.",
      "hidden_agenda": "They alter markers and ledgers to conceal select burials, protect old pacts, and prevent certain deaths from being traced."
    },
    {
      "name": "Ashford & Daughters Mourning House",
      "public_front": "A long-standing funeral home known for gentle rites, grief counsel, and immaculate arrangements for the coastal town.",
      "hidden_agenda": "They maintain a private annex of unregistered records and recovered items, tracking patterns of vanishings and the people who profit from them."
    },
    {
      "name": "The Brine-Choir",
      "public_front": "A quaint charitable society of tide-singers who bless sailors’ graves, fund memorials, and lead moonlit vigils at the shore.",
      "hidden_agenda": "They collect and barter secrets from the drowned, using buoy-bells and coastal rites to coerce favors and steer disappearances."
    }
  ]
}
```

Lanterns along Saltmarrow’s upper tiers have begun guttering blue, and fresh “restoration” work is appearing overnight: names shaved down, dates re-cut, whole family plots subtly rearranged. The Lanternward Society blames sea-salt and vandals, but Wren finds tool marks too precise to be weather. Meanwhile the Brine-Choir has announced a public Moon-Collecting Vigil after three fishermen washed ashore with their tongues stitched in brine-thread—an old warning. Ashford & Daughters is quietly locking its annex, as a brooding newcomer asks for Wren by name and offers a map that shouldn’t exist.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Blue-Guttering Lanterns",
      "description": "Lanterns in Saltmarrow Cemetery are burning with an unnatural blue sputter as headstones and plot boundaries are being altered overnight with expert precision.",
      "tensions": [
        "Lanternward Society insists it’s weather damage, but evidence suggests deliberate ledger-and-stone tampering",
        "Wren risks being blamed if her conservation work is used as cover for the edits",
        "Edited burials could erase the trail to her mother’s disappearance"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Moon-Collecting Vigil & the Brine-Thread Dead",
      "description": "The Brine-Choir calls a public shoreline vigil after three fishermen wash up with tongues stitched in brine-thread, while Ashford & Daughters seals its private annex and a brooding newcomer seeks Wren with an impossible cemetery map.",
      "tensions": [
        "The Choir’s ‘charity’ event is a bargaining signal, drawing townsfolk into a covert exchange of favors",
        "Ashford fears the vigil will expose unsanctioned records and relics tied to vanishings",
        "The newcomer’s map implicates someone inside the cemetery’s maintenance circle, putting Wren in immediate danger"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

